rComments: He was one of the most helpful teachers I had ever had. Really cares about students.
His exams were hard! But he was always willing to help students outside of class and in the office hours. My TA sucked and I would have failed the course, if it wasn't for his help.
It is just by luck to have such a Prof. so friendly, helpful, wise, knowlrdgeable and sympathatic.

He's a pretty good teacher overall.  Sometimes his notes are unorganized, but he goes over all the topic at a reasonable pace.  If you approch him with questions he'll try his best to answer them.  He sometimes goes offtopics but that's ok, makes the class a lot more interesting.
very caring and understanding professor.I enjoyed his course more than any other course.

Very helpful prof. Extremely reasonable & student-friendly. Provides his own notes if the material involves difficult reading. Grades tests promptly, and mercifully (based on level of difficulty). Also, extremely helpful in terms of flexibility to meet during office hours and before exams.
